\frac{x^n}{x+\alpha}=\frac{x^n-(-\alpha)^n}{x-(-\alpha)}+\frac{(-\alpha)^n}{x+\alpha}
\frac{1-r^n}{1-r}=\sum_{k=0}^{n-1}r^k
